WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.395
Why do highly competent managers consistently fail when attempting to

00:00:04.395 --> 00:00:08.790
scale their decision-making across boundaryless global enterprises? The failure stems

00:00:08.790 --> 00:00:13.185
from relying on linear managerial tactics in non-linear, culturally complex

00:00:13.185 --> 00:00:17.579
systems; success requires engineering an environment for active, self-built understanding.

00:00:17.579 --> 00:00:21.974
This is not a theoretical exercise. Mastering the causal mechanisms

00:00:21.974 --> 00:00:26.369
of global leadership is the direct path to professional mastery

00:00:26.369 --> 00:00:30.764
and self-actualization.
